### Description

I was using JavaScript Proxy to add some functionality to component via decorator:
```typescript
function proxyDecorator(target: any) {
    return new Proxy(target, {
        construct(target: any, argArray: any[], newTarget: Function): object {
            console.log(`proxy constructor`);
            return Reflect.construct(target, argArray, newTarget);
        }
    });
}

@proxyDecorator
@Component({
    selector: 'app-root',
// rest of component
```

The problem is it stopped to work since version 15. To reproduce the issue I created sample app via @angular/cli@14.0.0 and @angular/cli@15.0.0. You can see the result below:

![image](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/91020875/d1d3d638-3d4e-48b3-8bfe-793dfc43ab36)




